Marinka Gurewich (1902, Bratislava - 23 December 1990, Manhattan) was an American voice teacher and mezzo-soprano of Jewish Czech descent.
Her career as a singer in Germany was hindered by World War II and she fled Europe for the United States in 1940.
During the 1960s and 1970s she taught on the voice faculties of the Manhattan School of Music and the Mannes College of Music.
She continued to teach privately up until her death in 1990.
